find what youre looking for visit our equipment consultation page and fill out the equipment request form and we will help you get what you need looking to get into dtf printing heat transfer warehouse is your source for all direct to film printers equipment and supplies direct to film printing is a great way to add full color to your shop and allow you to do single piece proofing with your clients we have you covered with a variety of options from small to large format printers heat transfer warehouse currently carries the dtf station printer which is available in a small desktop version for the hobbyist as well as a larger version printer for commercial and professional uses dtf faqs what is a dtf printerdtf direct-to-film printers are a type of inkjet printer that are designed to print high-quality images directly onto a special film that can then be used for heat transfer applications onto various surfaces unlike traditional dtg direct-to-garment printers that print directly onto fabric dtf printers print onto a clear or opaque film that is then transferred onto the desired surface using a heat press dtf printers use a specialized ink set that is designed to adhere to the film and provide vibrant long-lasting prints the ink is typically formulated with a high density of pigment to provide deep rich colors that can withstand multiple washes and maintain their vibrancy over time one of the key benefits of dtf printing is that it can be used to print on a wide variety of surfaces including cotton polyester nylon leather and more this makes it a versatile printing method that is popular in the garment decorating industry to use a dtf printer you will need to purchase a dtf film load it into the printer and print your design using the specialized ink set once the design is printed onto the film it can be transferred onto the desired surface using a heat press the film adheres to the surface and becomes a permanent part of the fabric or materialoverall dtf printing is a popular alternative to traditional dtg printing that offers greater versatility and the ability to print on a wider range of materials what kind of printer do i need for dtf printinga dtf or direct to film printer is a printer specifically designed to use dtf inks and print dtf transfers we would recommend any of the printers listed above what kind of ink is used for dtf printing dtf direct-to-film inks are a specialized type of ink used in dtf printing these inks are designed to be used with dtf printers to produce high-quality vibrant images on a special film that can be transferred onto a variety of surfaces using a heat press dtf inks typically consist of a high-density pigment suspended in a water-based carrier solution the pigment is specially formulated to adhere to the dtf film and produce rich vibrant colors that can withstand multiple washes and maintain their vibrancy over time there are several types of dtf inks available on the market including eco-solvent uv-curable and water-based inks eco-solvent dtf inks are the most common type and are designed to work with a wide variety of dtf printers uv-curable dtf inks are a newer type of ink that offer faster drying times and increased resistance to fading and abrasion water-based dtf inks are another option that are environmentally friendly and produce high-quality long-lasting prints when choosing dtf inks it is important to consider factors such as color vibrancy wash fastness and compatibility with your specific dtf printer it is also important to follow the manufacturers instructions for storing and using the inks to ensure optimal performance and longevity is dtf printing the same as screen printingno dtf printing offers greater flexibility compared to screen printing as it allows you to apply designs in a wider range of areas on the shirt moreover in specific scenarios like small print runs dtf printing can be a more economical option than screen printing making it a cost-effective choice for many businesses × ok

price: now: $1899 - $3299 dtf station dtf supplies bundle w/ film sheets ink & cleaner msrp: was: price: now: $81606 direct to film dtf powder refers to a digital printing method used for textiles and other materials it is an alternative to traditional screen printing or heat transfer methods dtf powder involves printing an image onto a special film using a digital printer the film is then coated with a powdered adhesive which is typically a resin-based powder the powdered adhesive sticks to the ink on the film creating a design the excess powder is removed and the film is transferred onto the fabric using heat and pressure allowing the adhesive to bond with the fabric fibers once the film is transferred the adhesive is cured or set using a heat press or other curing methods this results in a permanent and vibrant design on the fabric dtf powder printing is known for its ability to produce detailed and high-quality prints including fine gradients and complex designs dtf powder printing has gained popularity due to its versatility durability and cost-effectiveness compared to traditional printing methods it can be used on various textiles such as cotton polyester blends and even leather additionally dtf powder printing allows for easy customization and quick turnaround times making it a popular choice for small businesses and individual entrepreneurs in the garment and textile industry × ok

$094 - $616 walakustom custom number dtf transfers msrp: was: price: now: $125 walakustom dtf transfers sample pack msrp: was: price: now: $500 about custom dtf transfers direct to film dtf transfers are a popular method of adding full-color designs onto garments bags and other textile items dtf transfers use a specialized dtf printer that prints the design onto a transfer sheet this sheet is then ready to press onto onto a garment using heat and pressure typically with heat press machine to create custom dtf transfers you will need the following components: design: first you will need to create your design using a compatible graphics software program make sure your design is in the appropriate format for printing and transfer heat press: you will need a heat press to apply your dtf transfer to your garment make sure your heat press is compatible with dtf transfers and has the appropriate temperature and pressure settings all dtf transfers come ready to press all you need to do is follow the application instructions and press to your garment how to apply your ready to press dtf transfer once you have recieved your ready to press direct to film dtf transfers follow these steps: cut out your design leaving a small border around the edges preheat your heat press to the appropriate temperature for your garment pre-press your garment on the heat press and preheat it for a few seconds to remove any wrinkles or moisture place your dtf transfer face down onto your garment making sure it is centered and straight apply heat and pressure to the transfer for the appropriate amount of time following the manufacturers instructions for your heat press and transfer sheet remove the transfer sheet from your garment and your custom dtf transfer is complete it is important to follow the manufacturers instructions for your dtf printer transfer sheet and heat press for best results additionally be sure to use high-quality materials and perform a test transfer on a small area before applying a larger design to ensure proper temperature pressure and transfer quality how to order custom dtf transfers heres how to order your walakustom direct to film dtf transfers from heat transfer warehouse: provide your design: provide your design in the appropriate format make sure to provide detailed information about the design including the size placement and any special instructions choose your transfer sheet: choose the appropriate dtf transfer sheet for your design and garment type heat transfer warehouse can provide guidance on the best transfer sheet for your specific needs specify your order details: provide details about the quantity of transfers needed confirm the order and payment: then we will get to work and get your dtf transfers on the way once your dtf transfers arrive: follow the the time and temp guide to apply your transfers × ok

& cleaner msrp: was: price: now: $81606 uninet uninet dtf triple coated transfer film msrp: was: price: now: $4799 - $12999 what is dtf film or direct to film film dtf film or direct-to-film film is a type of transfer film that is used in the dtf printing process it is a clear transparent film that has a special coating on one side that allows it to bond with dtf ink to use dtf film a design is first printed onto the film using a dtf printer and dtf ink the ink is then dried using a heat press or a special drying unit once the ink is dry the film is placed onto the garment or substrate to be printed and heat and pressure are applied using a heat press during the heat transfer process the ink on the film bonds with the substrate creating a permanent full-color transfer that is vibrant durable and long-lasting the dtf film can be peeled away from the substrate once the transfer is complete leaving behind a high-quality full-color image dtf film is available in a variety of sizes ranging from small sheets for custom designs to large rolls for mass production it is compatible with a wide range of substrates including cotton polyester and blends overall dtf film is a versatile and effective transfer film that is used in the dtf printing process to create high-quality full-color transfers on a wide range of substrates × ok

12 sheets msrp: was: price: now: $375 - $3750 about siser easyweed stretch siser easyweed stretch is a type of heat transfer vinyl htv that is designed to be applied to stretchy fabrics such as athletic wear spandex and lycra it is made from a thin flexible material that allows it to move and stretch with the fabric without cracking or peeling siser easyweed stretch is available in a wide variety of colors and finishes including matte glossy and metallic it can be cut using a vinyl cutter or plotter and is applied using a heat press or iron siser easyweed stretch is the top stretchable vinyl for your performance and active wear featuring a soft hand feel and light weight its cpsia certified which allows it to be safely used for any age garments along with those tougher material like spandex and lycra easyweed stretch delivers the stretch that you need along with all the qualities of the siser easyweed line of heat transfer vinyl its the thinnest vinyl line from siser at 85 microns and applies flawlessly on those cotton and poly blend garments it also has an ultra-matte finish with a soft hand feel available in a wide range of colors applying siser easyweed strech to apply siser easyweed stretch first cut the desired design in reverse using a vinyl cutter next use a weeding tool to remove any unwanted vinyl from the design place the design onto the fabric cover with a teflon sheet and apply heat using a heat press or iron according to the manufacturers instructions after the vinyl has been applied allow it to cool before removing the carrier sheet the result is a high-quality long-lasting design that will move and stretch with the fabric without cracking or peeling × ok

about dtf transfers & printing dtf or direct to film transfers are very economical durable easy to maintain and easy to use solution for custom transfers direct to film transfers are taking over the custom transfer industry because they have less restrictions on materials they can adhere to they look great on light and dark garments and dtf equipment have less frequent and easier maintenance than some alternatives direct to film also offers great possibilities for small orders and short turnarounds at your shop we also offer ready to press custom dtf transfers if you are looking for dtf transfers printed for you frequently asked questions: what are dtf transfersdtf or direct to film transfers are transfers printed onto a pet film then have a hotmelt adhesive powder applied to the transfer and finally are applied with a heatpress what is dtf printingdirect to film printing is the process of printing your transfer onto pet film so you can make a cost effective durable transfer how do i create dtf transfersthe first thing you need to make direct to film transfers is a good dtf printer check out our selection above on on our dtf printers page to see what best fits your needs you will also need high quality pet dtf film dtf inks and hotmelt adhesive dtf powder all of which generally are included in your dtf printer bundle purchase once you have you artworking printed you just need to apply the hot melt adhesive and apply the tranfser heat either with a dtf-specific curing oven or a heat press what is dtf powder dtf powder also known as a hot melt adhesive is an adhesive powder that is applied to a printed dtf transfer that creates an adhesive layer between the printed transfer ink and your garment when applied with heat it is usually shaken onto transfers after printing it is technically known as a thermoplastic polyurethane powder tpu how do you use dtf powderyou must apply the dtf powder to a print while it is still wet you want to evenly cover the entire printed area for best adhesion to the garment once the design is thoroughly covered and the excess powder is removed you must cure the powder at 315 degrees f to make the finish transfer ready to press onto your garment is dtf powder toxictpu is a completely inert material and does not off-gas toxic compounds however during the heating process there is potential to release methylene diphenyl diisocyanate which has an ndpa health rating of moderately hazardous so ventilation or n100 r100 or p100 respirator is recommended what is black dtf powder used forblack dtf powder is made to stop dye migration and block colors of the garment from showing though the transfer what is a dtf printera dtf or direct to film printer is a printer specifically designed to use dtf inks and print dtf transfers what kind of printer do i need for dtf transfersyou need a dtf printer specifcally designed for the dtf process we recommend the prestige a4 dtf printer × ok

embroidery supplies typically include: embroidery needles: these come in different sizes and are used to create different stitch sizes embroidery thread: these come in a variety of colors and materials such as cotton silk and rayon embroidery hoop: this is used to hold the fabric taut while you embroider they come in different sizes and shapes fabric: the type of fabric used depends on the project you are working on common choices include cotton linen and canvas embroidery scissors: these are small sharp scissors used to cut the embroidery thread transfer pen/pencil: this is used to transfer the design onto the fabric thimble: this is worn on your finger to protect it while you push the needle through the fabric optional supplies include: embroidery floss organizer: this is used to keep your embroidery thread organized embroidery stabilizer: this is used to stabilize the fabric while you embroider to prevent puckering lightbox: this is used to trace designs onto the fabric embroidery machine: this can be used to speed up the embroidery process for larger projects what suppliles do you need for a embroirdery machine if you are using an embroidery machine the supplies you need will differ slightly from traditional hand embroidery here are some supplies you may need: embroidery machine: this is the main tool you need for machine embroidery embroidery designs: these can be downloaded online and are used to create the embroidery designs embroidery thread: these come in a variety of colors and materials such as cotton silk and rayon bobbin thread: this is a special type of thread that goes in the bobbin and is used to create the embroidery design on the back of the fabric stabilizer: this is used to stabilize the fabric while you embroider to prevent puckering hoops: embroidery hoops are used to hold the fabric taut while the machine creates the embroidery design they come in different sizes and shapes embroidery scissors: these are small sharp scissors used to cut the embroidery thread cleaning supplies: to keep your embroidery machine in good working order you may need cleaning supplies such as brushes oil and lint rollers can i hand embroidery yes you can absolutely learn and practice hand embroidery hand embroidery is a beautiful and versatile craft that allows you to create unique designs and embellishments on various textiles with a few basic supplies and some practice you can learn to create beautiful embroidery designs by hand how do you thread my embroidery machine threading an embroidery machine can seem intimidating at first but with a little practice it becomes easier heres a basic guide to threading an embroidery machine: start by turning off your embroidery machine and raising the presser foot locate the spool holder and place your embroidery thread spool on it some embroidery machines have a separate spool holder for larger spools pull the thread through the thread guides on your machine these may be located on the top sides or front of the machine take the thread down to the tension discs passing it between them these discs will help regulate the amount of tension on the thread as it is being used pass the thread through the take-up lever which is a small hook or lever located near the upper thread guide thread the needle from front to back pulling the thread through the needle pull the thread towards the back of the machine and under the presser foot lower the presser foot and turn on your embroidery machine follow the instructions in your embroidery machine manual to select your design thread colors and other settings once youve threaded your embroidery machine a few times youll become more comfortable with the process remember to always follow the instructions in your machine manual to ensure you are threading your specific machine correctly how to thread a needle for embroidery threading a needle for embroidery can be a bit tricky but with a little practice you can do it easily here are the steps to follow to thread a needle for embroidery: cut a lenh of embroidery thread the lenh will depend on your project but its generally recommended to use a lenh of thread no longer than 18 inches to prevent tangling hold the end of the thread between your thumb and forefinger and wet it slightly with saliva or a damp cloth this will help the thread glide through the eye of the needle take the needle in your other hand and hold it with the eye facing up with your other hand bring the end of the thread close to the eye of the needle gently push the end of the thread through the eye of the needle you can also try using a needle threader which is a small tool that helps you thread the needle once the thread is through the eye of the needle pull it through until you have an equal lenh of thread on either side of the needle tie a knot at the end of the thread leaving a tail of about 1 inch your needle is now threaded and ready to use for embroidery remember to use the appropriate size needle and thread for your project and to practice different embroidery stitches to achieve various effects what is the most popular color for embroidery thread there isnt necessarily a most popular color for embroidery thread as the choice of thread color depends on the project the design and personal preference however there are some colors that are more commonly used than others here are some of the most commonly used colors in embroidery: black and white: these are versatile colors that can be used for outlines text or to add contrast to a design red: this is a popular color for floral designs and other designs that require a pop of color blue: blue is a calming color and can be used for designs related to nature or water green: green is commonly used for leaf and plant designs as well as nature scenes yellow: this color is great for adding brightness and sunshine to a design pink: pink is a popular color for floral and feminine designs purple: purple is associated with royalty and can add a touch of elegance to a design of course the choice of thread color ultimately depends on personal preference and the specific project dont be afraid to experiment with different colors and combinations to create unique and beautiful embroidery designs what is embroidery thread made out of embroidery thread can be made from a variety of materials each with their own unique properties and uses we sell polyester continuous filament because we believe that is the most versitial type how long is a embroidery thread spool the lenh of an embroidery thread spool can vary depending on the brand and the specific type of thread some spools may contain as little as 100 meters or around 110 yards of thread while others can have up to 5000 meters or around 5500 yards of thread we sell 5000 meter spools so you can avoid running out of thread in the middle of a job what is embroidery thread embroidery thread is a special type of thread that is used for embroidery it comes in a wide variety of colors materials and weights and is designed to add texture dimension and color to embroidered designsthere are several types of embroidery thread available including cotton silk rayon polyester and metallic each type has its own unique properties and is best suited for specific embroidery projectscotton embroidery thread is a popular choice for hand embroidery and is known for its softness and durability it is available in a wide range of colors and weightssilk embroidery thread is a luxurious and elegant option often used for high-end embroidery projects such as wedding gowns and other formal wearrayon embroidery thread is a shiny synthetic thread that is commonly used for machine embroidery it is known for its vibrant colors and high sheenpolyester embroidery thread is a versatile and durable option that is often used for both hand and machine embroidery it is available in a wide range of colors and weights and is known for its resistance to fading and shrinkagemetallic embroidery thread is a specialty thread that adds shimmer and shine to embroidered designs it is often used for decorative stitching and embellishmentsembroidery thread is available in skeins spools and cones and can be purchased from craft stores fabric stores and online retailers when selecting embroidery thread it is important to consider the type of embroidery project the fabric being used and the desired effect isacord embroidery thread is a high-quality durable thread that is commonly used for machine embroidery it is made from 100% polyester and is known for its strenh versatility and resistance to fading and shrinkingisacord thread is available in a wide range of colors with over 400 shades to choose from it comes in both mini-king spools and large cones making it easy to find the right amount of thread for any projectone of the unique features of isacord embroidery thread is its ability to run smoothly through embroidery machines without breaking or causing tension issues this makes it a popular choice among professional embroiderers and hobbyists alikeisacord thread is also known for its excellent color consistency which ensures that the same color is consistent across different spools and batches this is important when working on large projects or when using multiple spools of the same coloroverall isacord embroidery thread is a brother pe900 embroidery machine discover the joy of adding a personal touch to your projects with the brother pe900 embroidery-only machine unleash your creativity with 193 built-in embroidery designs 13 exquisite embroidery fonts or explore endless possibilities by downloading designs from the brother ibroidery platform² with the pe900 you can bring your ideas to life in record time thanks to its generous 5 x 7 embroidery area and impressive speed of up to 650 stitches per minute this embroidery machine is the perfect companion for any sewing room its sharp 37 lcd display provides a user-friendly interface for on-screen editing allowing you to effortlessly customize your designs whether its letter editing enhanced zooming resizing rotating repositioning or combining designs the pe900 empowers you to achieve your desired results hooping a 4 x 7 magnetic frame is a breeze with the ample 74 space from needle to arm ensuring convenient maneuverability advanced technology sets the pe900 apart when connected to a wireless network wireless lan enabled you can effortlessly transfer files from your pc to the machine using design database transfer¹ eliminating the need for usb connectivity this convenient software simplifies design management and with pe-design 11¹/² you gain even more flexibility and creative options additionally the artspira app¹ offers a world of possibilities allowing you to download embroidery patterns and create your own designs by drawing on your mobile device the app features intuitive drawing tools such as pens shapes and an eraser enabling you to create intricate line-art-inspired designs up to 5 x 7 130mm × 180mm once your masterpiece is complete the stitch simulator lets you preview how your design will look when stitched out you can also share your creations on various social media platforms directly from the app efficiency is key and the pe900 doesnt disappoint the advanced automatic needle threading feature streamlines the process of creating your projects saving you time and effort the built-in thread cutter button is a convenient time-saver ensuring smooth workflow importing designs is a breeze with the built-in usb port or you can explore over 5000 available designs on ibroiderycom for individual purchase the pe900s color sort feature intelligently adjusts the stitching order of multi-color designs reducing unnecessary color changes and maximizing efficiency additionally the jump stitch trimming function automatically trims excess thread jumps within each color enhancing the overall quality of your embroidery whether youre a seasoned embroidery enthusiast or just starting your journey the pe900 embroidery-only machine offers professional features at an affordable price prepare to expand your hobby and bring your imagination to life with this exceptional embroidery companion wireless lan with wireless lan enabled the pe900 will send you software update notifications and will let you send embroidery files from your pc to your machine via the free downloadable software design database transfer1 no usb required this allows for easy data management for all your designs and projects artspira app¹ draw your next project on the artspira app¹ with an array of patterns and cut data you can download plus the ability to make embroidery patterns by drawing on your mobile device and then transferring them to your pe900 wirelessly the artspira app¹ will have you creating on the go jump stitch trimming feature the pe900 has a handy jump stitch function which automatically trims any excess thread jumps within the color color sort the pe900 has color sort which adjusts the order in which multi-color embroidery designs are stitched thus reducing color changes and making it more efficient design database transfer transfer embroidery designs from your pc to your pe900 with the free downloadable software design database transfer¹ no usb required allows for easy data management for all your designs and projects built-in embroidery designs the pe900 has host of over 190 built-in embroidery designs ranging from decorative designs and patterns to ornate letters and flowers generous workspace when you are ready to step up and grow your hobby the pe900 has a generous 5” x 7” maximum embroidery area and a wonderful 74” from needle to arm which is the perfect amount of space to the right of the needle lcd display see your designs on the sharp 37” lcd display which allows for easy on-screen editing including letter editing enhanced zoom resizing rotating repositioning and combining designs included accessories: the pe900 comes with the following: embroidery foot “q” on machine needle set bobbin 4 one bobbin is on machine seam ripper scissors cleaning a job comes to you that you do not have the technology or equipment or capacity to tackle this is the time you should take a look at taking advantage of our custom transfers we have a great range of options to choose from to help you get that job done first let’s take a look at custom heat transfers custom heat transfers offer full color vinyl transfers printed with a wide format printer on printable htv this is great for doing patterns left chest logos t-shirt tags full front backpack bags etc and works on most garments or fabrics these transfers come cut weeded masked and ready to press all you need to do is remove the backing and press if you want to offer more to your customers check out our full-color digital sign vinyl which allows you to offer the customer not only the shirt they need but the option for a complete marketing package with transfers for their car laptop or windows etc custom sublimation transfers now let’s take a look at dye sublimation transfers these are also full color and can be used on only polyester garments or blends or polyester coated products because dye sublimation bonds directly to polyester through a gaseous process you can offer your customer full color on a garment or bag but you can also up-sell and offer them sublimation blanks whether that is photo panels key chains or koozies the list goes on and on rhinestone transfers one last type of custom transfers we offer is custom rhinestones these are rhinestone designs made to your specifications and will allow you to add that bling and sparkle of stones in your shop there is that demand out there for stones and they work great on cheer clothing or even some western type clothes crystal is the most popular color but keep in mind that these stones come in many sizes and colors resources × ok

decopress has a normal lead time of 2-5 days larger orders may take longer what level of detail can decopress reproduce we can print as small as 025 mm line thickness or 8 points on all patches what transfers are a type of heat transfer that uses a specialized film printed with a design using a dtf printer the design is then transferred onto a substrate using a heat press similar to other types of heat transfers like htv heat transfer vinyl or sublimation transfers to create a dtf transfer a design is printed onto a special dtf film using a dtf printer and dtf ink the printed film is then cut to the desired shape and size using a vinyl cutter or scissors the transfer is then placed onto the substrate such as a garment or bag and pressed using a heat press the heat press is set to a specific temperature and pressure which activates the adhesive on the film and transfers the design onto the substrate the transfer is then peeled away from the substrate leaving the design behind dtf transfers are known for their ability to produce high-quality vibrant prints on a wide range of substrates including cotton polyester nylon and more they are also ideal for printing on dark-colored fabrics since the film is opaque and can cover up the color of the substrateoverall dtf transfers are a popular option for printing custom designs onto a variety of substrates using a dtf printer and specialized film are these dtf transfers ready to pressyes all of our walastock transfers come ready to press what is a custom dtf transfera custom dtf transfer is made with the direct to film process and usually refer to ordering a custom design that is comes ready to press when you receive them visit our custom dtf transfers page featuring our walakustom transfers to order any design you have as a dtf print that is ready to press onto garments of your choice how long do dtf transfers lastour walastock transfers have been tested to 50+ domestic wash cycles they also have a 6+ month shelf life before being pressed × ok

1 manual tumbler press and walaoven bundle msrp: was: price: now: $54900 1 2 3 4 5 6 next heat press machine buying guide choosing the right heat press for your projects space and budget is important but we know the choices can be overwhelming here we’ll break down some of the biggest things to know and think about when shopping for a heat press this includes the types and sizes temp and pressure and features types of heat presses the first thing to consider is the type of heat press you need four main form factors are clamshell swing-away handheld and specialty presses clamshell heat presses are the most common and feature a hinged top plate that allows it to press down like a clamshell when the top plate is lowered the plate clamps shut applying even pressure and heat typically with a clamp to help maintain pressure swing-away heat presses have a movable top plate that swings to the side rather than a fixed hinge this allows for easier access to your work area on the lower plate without needing to work underneath a top plate the trade-off is that swing-away presses require more space to allow the top plate to rotate away handheld heat presses are common to see in big box retail stores and the size can be convenient but these have a few big tradeoffs to consider including temperature pressure and the smaller work-area the combination of the right temp and pressure is critical for your vinyl and transfers to properly stick and have a consistent product that lasts one of the most common issues among people starting out with htv and transfers is vinyl not sticking and peeling off garments due to not applying consistent and appropriate pressure and temperature for the transfer a standard style heat press eliminates these issues by providing a solid stable platform and consistent reliable heating surface and why we generally recommend these over handheld for most use-cases if you have the space while the size can make them convenient to store the smaller pressing area can also potentially limit your ability to make larger designs finally often the heating element behind the plate in these low-priced presses can be more inconsistent than a higher quality traditional press inconsistent heating of the plate can create cooler spots potentially creating a situation where you are actually pressing below your material temp specifications heat press sizes two big things to consider around heat press sizes are the size of designs and pressing area you want and the amount of space you have available smaller craft heat presses such as the 9 x 12 clamshell presses and handheld presses are good budget-friendly options if you don’t want a press to make up a lot of space or if you are doing small projects where you don’t need the versatility of having a larger plate and pressing-area we recommend measuring out these plate sizes and thinking about the designs you want to make now and in the future you can find some of these on our craft heat presses page mid-large sized heat presses typically include sizes from 15 x 15 heat presses through 16 x 20 these provide much more versatility for your projects with a bigger plate even if you don’t need them for your immediate project you typically have more options in this range including clamshell and swing-away and other options like auto-open timers the 16”x20” is a decent step up in size and overall footprint and we generally recommend these more for users who know they want the extra work-area space or for white toner printers as they make it easier to transfer a-b sheets we typically recommend this range for small businesses or users who just know they want the features or a larger work area these can be more suited towards garment businesses and people doing a lot of volume than for people just getting started wide format heat presses are large commercial heat presses usually for businesses generally they are much larger and more expensive and more suited for things like banners and flags temperature pressure & auto-open timers pressing your designs at the right temperature for the right amount of time and with enough pressure is critical for avoiding issues with adhesion and with your transfers to ensure you have a high-quality final product that lasts pressure application - one of the most common issues beginners run into is htv not sticking; often these users use handheld-style presses traditional hinge clamshell style presses feature adjustable pressure knobs that allow you to adjust your pressure prior to pressing your garment different materials can also specify different application pressures being able to adjust pressure test it and make sure it is applied consistently throughout the entire pressing duration can be helpful digital temperature controls allow you to be much more accurate than dial controls to ensure you are pressing at the right temperature for your materials this feature is quite common on most heat presses now and comes as a standard feature on all of our heat presses auto-open heat presses are typically clam-shell in style but usually feature a timer and hydraulic spring opening that automatically releases and opens after the appropriate pressing time this is a convenient feature so that you do not need to be watching the pressing time yourself or applying pressure this will allow you to multitask or prepare your next garment or transfer it’s a convenient nice-to-have option especially if you will be doing multiple back-to-back transfers or don’t want to have to track time separately other features materials quality & durability quality heating elements - a high-quality heating element with a large amount of coiling of the wires inside helps avoid cool spots increases reheating speed and heat retention as the press cools during a press can provide a more consistent temperature and is more reliable all of our heat presses feature quality heating elements this can also help with consistent transfers as they will have constant and even temperatures across the heating surface low-quality and cheaper heating elements can sometimes result in inconsistent heating across this plate resulting in cool spots that can be problematic for build material & wear - consider the materials a press is made out of most heat presses are made out of steel or aluminum but heat presses made with plastic bodies may not hold up well additionally we recommend looking for hydraulics rather than springs for the component that controls the opening and lowering of the top plate as springs can result in another wear and failure point all walapresses are built with steel bodies and with slow opening hydraulics along with most other presses we carry on our website threadable lower platens - this feature is available on some presses that allows you to press on only one side of a shirt by having additional room underneath the lower plate to thread the t-shirt around this is important for situations where you do not want both sides of the garment being exposed to heat or during certain applications like with sublimation frequently asked questions what is a heat press a heat press machine applies evenly distributed heat and pressure to blanks or garments to apply for vinyl and transfers how do you use a heat press first preheat your heat press to the temperature for the vinyl or material you are pressing which you can find on the product pages of our website or on our htv temp and time guide next arrange your shirt or garment on the heat press and pre-press your shirt for a few seconds then apply and arrange the transfer on your garment and press it for the appropriate time for your material also noted on the product pages and temp time guide what is a heat press machine used forheat presses are used to apply vinyl or a variety of different transfers what sizes of heat press machines are thereheat presses can vary significantly in size heat transfer warehouse offers 9x12 to a 44 x 64 twin heat press what is the best heat pressif you are a crafter or hobbyist we recommend a basic heat press such as our 9x12 craft press if you run a shirt-making business we recommend an auto open 16x20 heat press what supplies do i need for my heat press machinewe would recommend kraft paper/release sheets and platen covers all heat press accessories can be found here you will also need transfer and/or vinyl buying a heat press machine is a key purchase as always if you have questions please contact our customer service via chat or phone × ok

stahls hotronix heat presses are top-of-the-line machines that are widely used in the heat transfer industry they are known for their exceptional quality durability and versatility one of the key features of hotronix heat presses is their patented magnetic auto-open technology this feature allows the press to automatically open once the transfer process is complete eliminating the need for manual operation and reducing the risk of burns or other injuries this also ensures that the transfer is not overheated or overpressed resulting in a higher quality finished product hotronix heat presses also feature advanced digital controls which allow for precise temperature and time settings this ensures that the transfer is applied evenly and accurately resulting in a high-quality finished product in addition hotronix heat presses have adjustable pressure settings which make them suitable for a wide range of transfer applications from soft fabrics to hard substrates like ceramics and metal another key feature of hotronix heat presses is their durability they are constructed from high-quality materials and many models come with a lifetime warranty on their heating elements this makes them a long-term investment for businesses and individuals who require a reliable and durable heat press for their operations in addition to their quality and durability hotronix heat presses are available in a range of sizes and styles to suit different transfer applications and budgets from compact models for personal use to large industrial machines for high-volume production hotronix offers a range of options to meet the needs of its customers overall stahls hotronix heat presses are a popular choice for businesses and individuals who require a high-quality reliable and versatile heat press for their transfer applications here are some tips on how to pick the best stahls hotronix heat press machine for the job if you are looking for economy the maxx clam shell heat press machine is a great line with many great features like a digital timer and options for interchangeable platens which are great when doing bags or smaller areas like children’s clothing or sleeves the maxx presses come in a nice black powder coated finish and can handle pretty much any job in your shop if you are looking for something with more features and options i would definitely take a look at stahls hotronix auto open series of presses these have a digital read out and come in sizes from 11”x15” heat press up to a 16”x20” heat press but my favorite is the 16”x16” heat press because it is an all around great size to have in any shop the auto-open line also includes interchangeable platens if you are really looking to ramp up production in your shop i would take a gander at the stahls hotronix fusion iq heat press this is the most versatile machine on the market with so many unique features like drawer pull out or the swing away option which is great for dye sublimation the touch screen makes saving your most used settings and changing settings for a new product a breeze if you have a really high production shop then you need to look at the hotronix air fusion iq or the hotronix dual air fusion heat press machine these are the killer machines and help you get some serious production done whatever machine you choose i can say with confidence that you will be happy with a hotronix heat press machine fusion: the fusion is a high-end heat press with a touch screen display digital time and temperature controls and adjustable pressure it features a swing-away design and interchangeable platens making it versatile and easy to use air fusion: the air fusion is similar to the fusion but features pneumatic pressure control which allows for consistent pressure and reduces operator fatigue dual air fusion: the dual air fusion is a variation of the air fusion with two independently controlled platens that allow for increased productivity and efficiency auto open clam: the auto open clam is a popular choice for beginners and those with limited space with a hinged top that automatically opens when the timer is up maxx clam: the maxx clam is a heavy-duty heat press with a large platen size and adjustable pressure making it ideal for printing on a wide range of garment types and sizes hover: the hover is a unique heat press with a hover feature that allows for printing on uneven or raised surfaces such as buttons and zippers hotronix has all your heat press needs × ok

or experts they are easy to use and will help you get your heat transfer projects with products like the silhouette cameo 4 silhouette cameo 4 plus and other silhouette tools you will be ready for all heat transfer projects silhouette cameo 4 do you pick pink black or white when it comes to picking one of the most popular craft cutters on the market the silhouette cameo 4 or do you go for the cameo 4 plus which is 15” and the newest to craft worldthe silhouette cameo 4 comes pink white and black but the variety of color isn’t the only thing that makes this cutter one of the best crafting cutters on the market the cameo also comes in an extended width of 15” to really add production value to your small business already love the silhouette cameo because of an older model check out our blog comparing the cameo 3 and the cameo 4 to see if upgrading is the right choice for you the silhouette cameo 4 is the fourth generation of the popular electronic cutting machine designed for crafters hobbyists and diy enthusiasts it builds on the features of the previous cameo models while incorporating new and improved capabilities to enhance the user experience and increase the machines versatility the cameo 4 can cut a wide range of materials including paper cardstock vinyl fabric and more with a cutting width of up to 12-24 inches depending on the model you choose and a cutting lenh of up to 10 feetkey features of the silhouette cameo 4 include: increased cutting force: the cameo 4 has a cutting force of up to 5000 grams which is significantly more powerful than its predecessors this increased force allows the machine to cut thicker and denser materials with ease faster cutting speeds: the cameo 4 boasts faster cutting speeds than previous models allowing for quicker project completion and improved efficiency tool type detection: the cameo 4 features an innovative tool type detection system that automatically detects the tools being used in the machine and adjusts the settings accordingly autoblade: the cameo 4 comes with an updated autoblade which automatically adjusts the blade depth based on the material being used ensuring precise cuts without the need for manual adjustments dual motor system: the cameo 4 has a dual motor system which provides more precise and accurate cutting especially when working with intricate designs and patterns built-in roll feeder and crosscutter: the cameo 4 includes a built-in roll feeder and crosscutter for cutting rolled materials like vinyl and heat transfer material directly from the roll making it easier to manage larger projects wireless connectivity: the cameo 4 can connect to your computer or device wirelessly via bluetooth allowing for cable-free design transfer and operation touchscreen interface: the machine features a built-in touchscreen interface for easy navigation and control compatibility with silhouette studio: the cameo 4 is compatible with the silhouette studio software which provides a range of design tools functions and access to the silhouette design store to get started with your silhouette cameo 4 follow the same steps outlined in the previous response for the general silhouette cameo making sure to refer to the cameo 4 user manual for any model-specific instructions or information the silhouette cameo 4 offers a powerful and versatile cutting experience for a wide range of creative projects from paper crafting to fabric and vinyl applicationsto get started with your silhouette cameo follow these steps: unbox and set up the machine according to the instructions provided in the user manual install the silhouette studio software on your computer or device you can download the software from the silhouette website connect your silhouette cameo to your computer or device using a usb cable or bluetooth launch the silhouette studio software and create or import the design you want to cut load the material you want to cut onto the cutting mat making sure its properly aligned and adhered adjust the settings in silhouette studio to match the material youre using and send the design to your cameo for cutting once the cutting is complete carefully remove the material from the cutting mat and weed away any excess material from your design if needed transfer the design to your project using transfer tape or other appropriate methods depending on the material youve used the silhouette cameo is a versatile cutting machine that offers a wide range of creative possibilities for various types of projects from paper crafting to fabric and vinyl applications who is silhouette americasilhouette america is a company that specializes in designing and manufacturing electronic cutting machines and related accessories for crafters hobbyists and diy enthusiasts the company is best known for its silhouette cameo series of cutting machines which are popular for their versatility ease of use and wide range of applications in various crafting projectsin addition to the silhouette cameo machines the company also offers other cutting machines such as: silhouette portrait: a smaller more compact cutting machine designed for portability and smaller projects it can cut materials up to 8 inches wide and 12 inches long silhouette curio: a multi-purpose machine that not only cuts but also embosses etches and performs other functions making it ideal for mixed-media projects along with cutting machines silhouette america offers a range of accessories and tools to enhance the crafting experience such as: cutting mats: these mats are designed to hold materials in place during the cutting process and come in various sizes and adhesive strenhs blades and tools: the company offers a variety of blades and tools for different cutting applications including fabric deep-cut and premium blades pens and sketch pens: these pens can be used with silhouette machines for drawing sketching and writing directly onto materials specialty media: silhouette america provides various specialty materials such as adhesive vinyl heat transfer vinyl printable materials and more for use with their cutting machines software and digital designs: the company offers the silhouette studio software which is used to create and edit designs for cutting on silhouette machines additionally they maintain the silhouette design store an online marketplace where users can purchase and download thousands of digital designs for use in their projects silhouette america is dedicated to providing innovative and user-friendly crafting solutions to help individuals express their creativity and bring their ideas to life their range of cutting machines accessories and software cater to various crafting needs and offer endless possibilities for $13100 price: now: $10500 - $42000 1 2 3 4 5 6 next what is sublimation sublimation printing is an advanced digital printing technique that utilizes specially formulated heat-sensitive inks to transfer stunning designs onto an array of materials this innovative process involves the conversion of ink particles directly into gas by applying heat which permeates the polymer coating or fibers of the substrate and solidifies into the material the result is a breathtakingly vivid sharp and long-lasting print that seamlessly integrates into the fabric thanks to its incredible ability to replicate intricate and full-color designs with exceptional accuracy sublimation printing is a highly sought-after method for creating customized apparel promotional items and one-of-a-kind gifts sublimation tools heat transfer warehouse offers a wide selection of premium printers such as the sawgrass sg1000 sublimation printer pair this printer with sublimation paper from walasub and excellent sublimation ink like our siser easysubli ink to bring your designs to life we also offer a variety of blanks ranging from t-shirts to hard blanks like our steel skinny 20 oz tumbler with straw dye sublimation printing offers the ability to create beautiful full-color prints that will not only last but will wow anyone who sees them if you want more information on the dye printing check out our youtube playlist for more in-depth knowledge sublimation resources faqs what is sublimation sublimation is a printing method that utilizes heat to imprint a design onto fabric or other materials the design is printed onto specialized paper using sublimation ink and then placed onto a blank material upon application of heat the ink transforms into gas and firmly bonds with the materials surface resulting in a permanent and high-quality print that is robust and long-lasting how does sublimation work sublimation unlike heat transfer vinyls uses heat to turn sublimation ink into a gas which is able to permeate the pores of the material you are printing on this results in the design and the material becoming a cohesive item sublimation printing allows for permanent designs similar to a tattoo where as heat transfer vinyl will still be sitting on the surface of the garment or blank why would i use sublimation sublimation allows you to print any designs permanently in any color you want unlike vinyl printing sublimation is not limited to the brand of vinyl you purchase which gives you the ability to print any design in any color combination you want what materials can i use for sublimation printing sublimation works best with clothing garments made from polyester or hard surface polymer-coated items these would be products such as coffee mugs t-shirts mouse pads and more can i use sublimation printing on dark fabric fabrics that are already colored are not great candidates for sublimation as the material already has color if you want to create custom clothing that is dark we recommend using heat transfer vinyls what printers are best for sublimation printing if you are a beginner or hobbyist we recommend a printer from sawgrass if you are looking to create large batch order epson printers are a great option how long does sublimation last sublimation printing is a great option if you want your designs to last a long time since sublimation printing uses heat to transfer dye into the fabric or surface it creates a bond making the design seem to be a part of the fabric or surface it wouldnt be surprising to see it last for 10 years or longer without fading why is my image ghosting the transfer is moving while heated and transferring dye either you are pressing moving then pressing again or you are peeling while hot and then laying the hot paper back down why are my images coming out blurry if your images are coming out blurry it is likely a printer problem i would first recommend making sure you have a high res / good quality image then double check that your printer nozzles / heads are clean what time temp & pressure is best for applying sublimation for soft garments: 385 for 45 seconds medium pressure for hard blanks: 400 for 60 seconds medium pressure × ok

sublimation printer is a desktop printer that is specifically designed for use with sublimation ink and transfer paper it is a popular choice for small businesses hobbyists and individuals who are looking for an affordable and easy-to-use sublimation printing solution the sg500 features sawgrasss virtuoso print manager software which is designed to make it easy to set up and manage print jobs the software includes a range of templates and design tools making it easy to create and print high-quality designs the sg500 also features sawgrasss sublijet-uhd sublimation ink which is designed to easy to fit into small spaces such as a home office or small business it also offers a relatively low cost of ownership with affordable ink cartridges and low maintenance requirements overall the also available in bundles with different heat presses and sublimation ovens faqs what is sublimation printingsublimation ink can convert from a solid to a gas without going through the liquid form which allows you to apply an image to specially coated materials using heat and pressure for more information check out our what is sublimation blog what is a sublimation printersublimation printers are printers that are specifically designed for use with sublimation ink and transfer paper they are used to create high-quality full-color designs that are transferred onto a range of substrates including fabrics ceramics metals and moresublimation printers work by heating up the ink which then turns into a gas and is transferred onto the substrate through a process called sublimation the ink is absorbed by the fibers of the substrate resulting in vibrant and long-lasting colors that are resistant to fading and wearthere are two main types of sublimation printers: desktop printers and wide-format printers desktop sublimation printers are smaller and more affordable making them a popular choice for small businesses and individuals who are just starting out with sublimation printing they are designed to print onto smaller substrates such as mugs phone cases and t-shirtswide-format sublimation printers on the other hand are larger and more expensive but they offer a larger print bed and the ability to print onto larger substrates such as banners flags and upholstery fabrics they are typically used by larger businesses and manufacturers who need to produce larger quantities of sublimated productssome popular brands of sublimation printers include epson sawgrass and ricoh when choosing a sublimation printer it is important to consider factors such as print quality speed connectivity and compatibility with different types of ink and transfer paper can you use regular ink for sublimation printingno you need to use an ink specifically designed for the sublimation process what kinds of sublimation printers are availableheat transfer warehouse offers the sawgrass sg500 the sawgrass sg1000 and the epson surecolor f570 how do you use a sublimation printerfirst you will want to create a design to print then size your design for the garment you intend to sublimate next you will want to have the transfer media ready in your printer and you your printers software to print your design can you use a regular printer for sublimationalthough it is possible to convert some desktop inkjet printers to sublimation it is a much better option to just buy a purpose built sublimation printer what sizes can you print with a sublimation printerthe sg1000 prints on media up to 11 x 17 the sg500 prints on media up to 85x 14 and the epson surecolor f570 can printer on media up to 24 in width × ok

deciding between siser easysubli vs sawgrass sublijet-uhd inks can i use the bypass tray with the sg500 the sawgrass bypass tray allows you to make larger prints and bigger paper 85 x 51” for the sg500 same width and up to 13 x 51” for the sg1000 the bypass tray is only able to extend the width of prints on the sg1000 model printer while technically compatible with the sg500 it does not extend the width and only supports the existing 85” width capacity with a total dimension support of 85” x 51” where do i set up my training and installclick this link to set up a training and installation what kind of computer or software do i need to run the sg500computer: windows 11 windows 10 recommended windows 8 81 10 mac oc 1014 or later recommended ram 8gb min 2g as for software sawgrass print manager comes free with the purchase of a sawgrass printer along with sawgrass creative studio how big of a print can i print with the sg500there are two sizes you can print with the sg500 you can print 85x11 and 84x14 you can use the sg500 bypass tray to print up to 85 x 51” if you are hoping to print larger sizes this is one of the main differences with the bigger sg1000 model which can print up to 11” x 17” with the standard tray and up to 13”x51” with the addition of the sawgrass bypass tray can i switch my ink typesince ink conversion can be extremely hard on the printhead and run the risk of chemical mixture and clogging changing ink types ie chromablast sublijet easysubli can cause major damage to the printhead and for this reason will void the remainder of the warranty so it is possible to switch inks but the warranty will be voided and you run the risk of printhead damage should i get the siser easysubli or sawgrass sublijet-uhd ink bundleeasysubli inks are optimized for use with siser easysubli sublijet inks are optimized for the highest quality prints for sublimation directly to polyester we recommend considering what you will primarily be printing on and how you will be transferring your sublimation prints easysubli inks are optimized for use with siser easysubli sublimation paper and recommended if that is your primary method for sublimation learn more about siser easysubli here sawgrass sublijet inks are the sawgrass standard inks and are optimized for the highest quality prints for sublimation directly to polyester why are the ink levels not 100% on my new printerthe first time your ink is placed into your printer it pulls the ink into the cartridges and fills your ink lines this can cause the ink levels to not read 100 % dont worry the missing percentage of your ink is in your printer ready to use how many prints can i get out of my ink cartridgessince everyone doesnt print the same images because of this estimating the number of prints that can be achieved on a single set of cartridges is not possible do i need to leave my printer powered on whywhen the printer is powered off the printer wont be able to run automatic maintenance cycles these cycles are important to keep your printer in the best condition and to prevent clogging within the printer lines what materials can i press with my printeryou can use texprint-sawgrass sublimation paper texprintdt light epson sublimation paper walasub paper and siser easysubli sheets to press onto white and light colored polyester garments how do i contact sawgrass if my printer is experiencing issuesyou can contact and file a ticket with sawgrass on their website

sublimation ink is a popular choice for dye-sublimation printing and is known for its high quality vibrant colors and long-lasting results however it is important to note that not all epson printers are compatible with sublimation ink so it is important to check the manufacturers specifications before purchasing and using epson sublimation ink faq what is sublimation inksublimation ink is a type of ink that is used in dye-sublimation printing a process that involves printing a design onto a special transfer paper and then transferring the design onto a substrate such as fabric or ceramics using heat and pressuresublimation ink is unique in that it can convert from a solid to a gas without passing through a liquid phase a process known as sublimation when sublimation ink is heated to a high temperature the ink turns into a gas and is absorbed into the substrate where it cools and solidifies creating a permanent and vibrant imagesublimation ink is typically used in printers that are specifically designed for dye-sublimation printing and it is available in a range of colors because sublimation ink is absorbed into the substrate rather than sitting on top of it like traditional inks it produces high-quality long-lasting images that are resistant to fading peeling and crackingsublimation printing is commonly used for producing high-quality and durable prints on a variety of products including t-shirts mugs mouse pads phone cases and more however it is important to note that sublimation printing is only suitable for certain types of materials that are capable of absorbing the sublimation ink and it may not be the best option for all printing needs how long does sublimation ink last in the cartridgefrom the time that we get them from our vendor these inks should have a 18 month to 2 year expiration date on it they also last about 6 months after they are installed into your printer how long does sublimation ink last once pressed sublimation prints begin to fade when the fabric begins to fade can you use sublimation ink on printable vinylyes you can using sublimation ink on sublimation vinyl is the best way to use sublimation designs on 100% cotton we recommend using frosty clear is infusible ink the same as sublimation inkyes infusible ink is cricuts version of sublimation infusible inks are limited to the colors offered by cricut can you remove sublimation ink once it is pressedif sublimation is applied to polyester or other types of polymers it will become permanent and cannot be undone unlike other types of ink sublimation ink cannot be removed with bleach however on cotton fabric sublimation ink may fade after several washes on hard surfaces such as poly-coated coffee mugs sublimation can be reduced with high heat but the only way to completely eliminate it is by sanding down the coating to reveal the underlying ceramic what fabrics does sublimation ink work onsublimations work best with 100% polyester but they also work great with polyester blends can you use sublimation ink on cottonyes but they will not be as vibrant or robust as a poly blend if you need to use cotton we recommend using a sublimation htv or go fuze™ sublimation to cotton solution can you mix different brands of sublimation ink in your printerits not recommended to mix sublimation inks from different brands each brand of sublimation ink has its own unique formula that is specifically designed to work with their printers and paper mixing different brands of sublimation ink can lead to issues with your printer and result in low-quality prints × ok

color of the stone the origins of rhinestonesthe origins of rhinestones are not entirely clear but they are believed to have been first made in bohemia which is now part of the czech republic the bohemian region was known for producing high-quality glass and it is believed that the first rhinestones were made there in the 1700s by glassmakers who were experimenting with new techniques for cutting and faceting glassthe name rhinestone comes from the rhine river which runs through the area where the stones were first produced the popularity of rhinestones grew in the early 1900s when they were used in the fashion industry to create jewelry and other accessories frequently asked questions what are rhinestones rhinestones are diamond or gemstone simulants they are made of acrylic and offer an impressive shine how to make a rhinestone template what will you need rhinestone software vinyl cutters heat presses hot fix rhinestones flock big enough for your design - we used template flock ktm rhinestone transfer masks rhinestone template board rhinestone brush tweezers squeegee 1 load your flock in the cutter face up 2 export your rhinestone design to your preferred cutting software and send to your cutter normally template flock is cut at at a heavier pressure and uses a 60 degree blade 3 peel the flock from its liner this will reveal the holes that you have cut in your cutter which will act as your stone placements 4 place the flock sticky side down on your template board 5 pour rhinestones on your board and gently brush the rhinestones across your design using a rhinestone brush do this until they each have a spot in one of the stone placement holes in your flock often many of the rhinestones will fall into the holes the proper way however some stones will likely fall upside down or may too stubborn to even fall into a hole in that case a tweezers may be needed to properly place some rhinestones in their place 6 now that your stones are in place grab your ktm rhinestone transfer mask and peel it off its liner place it carefully on top of the rhinestone design 7 apply firm pressure across the entire design to ensure that the rhinestones stick to the ktm mask for smaller designs you can use your hand; however for larger designs we recommend using a squeegee 8 peel the ktm mask away from the flock in a smooth motion if you find that not all rhinestones are sticking to the ktm mask simply lay the mask back down and apply more pressure in that area 9 now that your rhinestone design is on the ktm mask if you aren’t ready to press your design place the mask back on its liner and save until you’re ready to press you may notice that the orange fibers from the template flock are sticking to the ktm mask no worries these orange fibres will not stick to your garment when pressing if you are ready to press go to the next step 10 place your design on your garment and press at 305 degrees for 10-15 seconds it is very important to peel cold what are ab rhinestones aurora borealis ab is the most beloved crystal color for dance and performance costumes the ab coating is an iridescent rainbow-like coating that mimics the northern lights what are heat press rhinestones heat press rhinestones are a type of heat transfer that allows for the application of rhinestone designs onto garments using a heat press rhinestones are small sparkly gems that can be arranged into various shapes and designs to create a glamorous and eye-catching effectto create heat press rhinestones a design is first created using specialized software and a vinyl cutter to create a stencil of the design rhinestones are then arranged onto the stencil and a heat transfer tape is applied over the top to hold the rhinestones in place the design is then transferred onto the garment using a heat pressheat press rhinestones are popular for creating custom apparel with a touch of glamour and sparkle they are commonly used for dance and cheerleading uniforms as well as for custom t-shirts hats and more rhinestone designs can be simple or complex and can be applied to a wide range of garment types including cotton polyester and blendssome benefits of using heat press rhinestones include: glamorous and eye-catching designs: rhinestones add a touch of glamour and sparkle to custom apparel designs making them stand out and draw attention durability: heat press rhinestones are durable and can withstand frequent washing and wear versatility: rhinestone designs can be applied to a wide range of garment types making them versatile and suitable for a variety of applications customization: rhinestone designs can be customized to create unique and personalized designs that are perfect for special events or occasions we recommend using walastone heat press rhinestones for custom apparel designs that require a touch of glamour and sparkle they are durable versatile and can be customized to create unique and personalized designs please check out our stock designs as well as our loose stones how to rhinestone a shirt check out our blog on how to make a rhinestone transfer herenow to apply the transfer lint roll your garment first then line up the rhinestone transfer where you would like it on your shirt once your transfer is where you want it press it according to the application instructions which are: firm pressure at 305 f for 15 seconds don’t forget that rhinestones are a cold peel so wait until the transfer is room temperature before peeling what are rhinestones made of they are typically made of acrylic or glass how do you press heat press rhinestones prepare the transfer tape: cut a piece of heat transfer tape to fit the size of the stencil and remove the backing paper from the tape transfer the design onto the garment: place the transfer tape with the rhinestone design onto the garment with the rhinestones facing down onto the garment apply heat and pressure using a heat press remove the transfer tape: once the transfer tape has cooled down gently peel off the transfer tape to reveal the rhinestone design on the garment when pressing rhinestones it is important to use the appropriate temperature pressure and time settings on the heat press to ensure that the rhinestones adhere properly to the garment it is also important to use the appropriate transfer tape for the rhinestones being used to ensure that the rhinestones transfer cleanly and easily onto the garment can i use template flock with rhinestones yes template flock is needed to make a rhinestone template you can see the the required materials and steps to create a template listed above what temp do you press heat press rhinestones you should always check the application instructions on the product page of the exact stones you purchased but the typical temperature range is 300f to 355f what is a rhinestone a rhinestone is a small faceted gem made of glass acrylic or crystal they are typically used for decorative purposes such as in jewelry or apparel rhinestones can come in a wide range of colors shapes and sizes and can be used to create intricate and eye-catching designs rhinestones are commonly used in the fashion industry for adding a touch of glamour and sparkle to clothing such as on dance costumes evening gowns and other formal wear they can also be used for accessorizing jewelry handbags shoes and other fashion accessories rhinestones are often used in combination with other materials such as sequins beads or embroidery to create intricate and eye-catching designs they are also commonly used in heat transfer designs for apparel such as with heat press rhinestones where they can be arranged into various shapes and designs to create a glamorous effect rhinestones are a popular decorative element in the fashion industry known for their versatility sparkle and ability to add a touch of glamour to any design × ok

way to incorporate full color images into your garment decorating we have a variety of papers for both inkjet and laser printers that will add a new dimension of value to your garments all of these papers can be used at home with a basic printer we offer several brands of transfer paper for both light-colored garments and for dark-colored garments that are compatible with numerous fabrics printable heat transfer paper is great for adding photos or other photo realistic elements to designs it’s perfect for those one time events such as family and class reunions or even memorial shirts for a loved oneneenah is a popular brand of inkjet heat transfer paper that we carry available in packs of 100 and sample packs for testing or short runs we also have our own in-house brand walapaper that comes in packs of 50 as well as a sample packs of 10 for testing both walapaper and neenah inkjet paper offer great opacity and will last up to 30 washes while still having a soft feel on your shirtsmaybe laser printers are more your style and if that’s the case we have paper for you too we offer neenah and forever laser paper including forever flex-soft no cut paper that is great for those really complicated one color designs that you couldn’t pay us to weed forever flex-soft also has the added bonus of adhering to hard surface items such as wood and ceramic surfaces many of these papers come in a sample pack as well as packs of 100 or packs of 25 for the forever flex-soft laser heat transfer paper for both lights and darks will last up to 40 washes and have options for both light and dark garments types of transfer paper: there are a few considerations for purchasing heat transfer paper for home desktop printers when buying and using heat transfer paper you need to consider two things your printer type and whether your garment that youll be applying your design to is light or dark most of our transfer papers are labeled either light or dark and specialzied for the level of opacity needed for these different shirt colors shop by garment color: light transfer paper dark transfer paper shop by printer type: inkjet transfer paper laser transfer paper shop by brand: walakut transfer paper neenah transfer paper forever transfer paper heat transfer paper faqs what is iron on transfer paper iron-on transfer paper also known as iron-on transfer sheets or iron-on decals is a type of specialty paper that allows you to transfer designs images or text onto fabric or other compatible surfaces using heat from a household iron it is commonly used for creating personalized t-shirts bags pillows and other fabric items how do you use heat transfer paper design your artwork: create or select the design you want to transfer onto the fabric you can use graphic design software or choose from pre-designed templates print your design: load the iron-on transfer paper into your inkjet or laser printer depending on the type of transfer paper you have ensure that youre using the appropriate print settings recommended by the transfer paper manufacturer for optimal results mirror your design optional: some iron-on transfer papers require you to reverse or mirror your design before printing this step is necessary when your design includes text or if you want the final transferred image to face the correct direction when applied to the fabric check the instructions provided with the transfer paper to see if mirroring is required trim the design: once you have printed your design onto the transfer paper carefully cut around the edges of the design leaving a small border if necessary preheat your iron: set your household iron to the appropriate temperature setting recommended by the transfer paper manufacturer make sure to choose the setting suitable for the fabric youre using position the transfer: place the fabric item on a flat heat-resistant surface position your printed design onto the fabric ensuring it is placed in the desired location apply heat and pressure: place a thin cloth or parchment paper over the design to protect it and the iron firmly press the iron down on the transfer applying steady pressure move the iron around the design ensuring that you cover the entire surface area follow the recommended heat and pressing time specified by the transfer paper manufacturer allow it to cool and peel: after the specified time remove the iron and allow the transfer to cool for a few seconds slowly peel off the backing paper starting from one corner and pulling at a 180-degree angle be careful not to disturb the transferred design finalize the process: after removing the backing paper check the transferred design for any imperfections or incomplete transfers if necessary repeat the heat transfer process using additional heat and pressure its important to note that the specific instructions and recommendations may vary depending on the brand and type of iron-on transfer paper you are using always refer to the manufacturers guidelines for the best results × ok
