what is heat transfer vinyl heat transfer vinyl or htv is a type of vinyl material that is used to create designs or graphics on fabrics the vinyl is cut into the desired design using a vinyl cutter then the excess vinyl that is not part of the design is removed or “weeded” away and finally the vinyl is applied to the fabric using a heat press the heat and pressure cause the vinyl to adhere to the fabric creating a permanent and durable design heat transfer vinyl comes in various colors finishes and textures such as matte glossy metallic glitter and more and allows for intricate designs and vibrant colors it is a popular choice for creating custom designs on t-shirts hats bags team uniforms personalized gifts and promotional products is heat transfer vinyl the same as iron-on vinyl yes the term iron-on vinyl refers to heat transfer vinyl often shortened to htv the phrase iron-on is often used in the crafter and hobby community as this material can technically be applied with an iron instead of a heat press as a way to get started using htv – however there can be downsides to using irons rather than a heat press designed for this application it is often difficult to apply enough consistent pressure or high enough temp which can result in adhesion issues and for best results we recommend a traditional heat press what is the difference between heat transfer vinyl and craft vinyl or permanent vinyl craft vinyl adhesive vinyl or permanent vinyl generally refer to “sticker” vinyl with an adhesive backing while the process of creating designs and cutting the vinyl is similar craft adhesive vinyl is intended to be directly applied to materials like a sticker decal without applying heat heat transfer vinyl does not have an adhesive backing and heat is required to apply the material htv is also mostly geared towards application on fabric and garments where craft vinyl is often used for hard surfaces for decorative purposes what is the difference between heat transfer vinyl and printable vinyl / what is printable vinyl printable vinyl is a printable htv that either you can receive with already printed designs ready to be pressed or as the blank materials to be printed on with specialized printers and ink the printable vinyl we sell is typically used and designed for high end commercial printers and not for consumer inkjet printers for standard desktop laser or inkjet printers you can use heat transfer paper which can be good for one-off quick projects or hobby craft projects if you are looking for printable htv check out our selection of ready to press patterns or our custom transfers and print on demand service can i use an iron or do i need a heat press or t-shirt press machine htv can technically be applied with an iron instead of a heat press as a way to get started using htv – however there are downsides to using irons rather than a heat press designed for this application it is often difficult to apply enough consistent pressure or high enough temp which can result in adhesion issues can you remove htv from a shirt or garment yes it is possible to remove htv from a shirt using htv vinyl remover to do so turn the garment inside-out apply the remover to the backside where the vinyl is adhered and let it soak through flip the garment back to normal and stretch the garment in 4 directions which should begin to loosen the material you should not be able to peel off the vinyl is there a certain temperature needed for htv yes each material has a recommended temperature time needed for the press level of pressure and whether it should be peeled hot or cold see the application instructions on our product pages or view our htv temp and time guide how do i prevent my htv from peeling why is my vinyl not sticking if your vinyl is peeling it can be from not enough time/heat/pressure too much heat or if the vinyl was applied to a seam or uneven area too high of a temp or too long of an application can overheat adhesive and cause adhesion issues and too much pressure can squeeze out adhesive making it less effective any seam or unevenness can also cause the possibility of the material not laying flat and having a gap underneath the vinyl an uneven area can also include if the shirt is not laid even on your heat press where material could be bunched underneath how long does htv last for the most part htv properly applied with a heat press will outlive the lenh of the shirt the key here is to make sure you are using the correct amount of pressure and heat and following the appropriate instructions for the material often where there are peeling or other life issues it is a result of applying the material incorrectly with too little pressure or too much heat this can be a common result of using a handheld heat press or iron rather than traditional heat press and why we recommend investing in a quality heat press do i need stretch htv for garments that stretch a little bit everything vinyl and garment will have a little bit of stretch to them and does not mean you require a stretch htv most shirts will stretch about 10-20% and most vinyl will have some stretch and work perfectly fine for these types of garments stretch is more often suited towards highly stretchy materials with lots of rebound such as stretchy athletic shorts yoga tights and pants and compression shirts however you can definitely still use stretch htv on most regular standard garments if you prefer and dont want to worry about it one recommendation if you are applying htv to a stretchy garment like the above is to consider applying the design with a little bit of stretch to match the state the garment will be in when worn to avoid the design being deformed otherwise if you apply a design in a non-stretched state and when worn is always stretched as in the case of yoga pants your design may look deformed and stretched out can you cut htv by hand if you don’t have a vinyl cutter you can technically use a scissors or hobby/exacto knife to attempt to manually cut a design if you are able to draw or cut a design directly onto the vinyl however using a vinyl cutter designed for cutting digital designs is highly recommended the process of trying to hand cut an htv design is tedious prone to error or unclean cuts and not feasible for many types of designs do you leave backing on when cutting yes the clear backing is your carrier that is used to help feed the material through your cutter and you always want the carrier side down so your vinyl surface is on top and the cutter is cutting through the htv surface and not the carrier backing this keeps the design together upon cutting we always recommend doing a test cut to ensure youre not cutting through the carrier material and are comfortable with the process before cutting multiple quantities or a large design using parchment paper between htv and press do you need parchment paper parchment paper or non-stick sheet will not hurt however you often do not need parchment with the carrier sheet backing on your htv if this is intact and fully covers your design if you are doing multiple layers be aware that it can cause your vinyl to have an unnecessary shine that you may not like due to the glossy side sometimes imparting on the vinyl through multiple presses if you would like a protective layer between your heat press or are worried about it you can also always purchase a teflon cover for your heat press using parchment paper between htv and press do you need parchment paper parchment paper or non-stick sheet will not hurt however you often do not need parchment with the carrier sheet backing on your htv if this is intact and fully covers your design if you are doing multiple layers be aware that it can cause your vinyl to have an unnecessary shine that you may not like due to the glossy side sometimes imparting on the vinyl through multiple presses if you would like a protective layer between your heat press or are worried about it you can also always purchase a teflon cover for your heat press can you layer htv yes you can definitely layer htv designs there are a few things to be aware of that we’ve listed below but if you want more information on layering please see our layering htv guide a few big things to be aware of are compatible materials considerations for inlay vs layering and application first you should make sure the htv you are using are compatible with each other and can be layered some materials like glitter can’t be layered on top of but can be the final top layer on other materials as a rule of thumb we don’t recommend layering htv with textured vinyl if a vinyl is not layerable you can try an inlay method instead laying vinyl next to each other rather than on top for application as always when layering you will want to use a quick tack method of 1-2 seconds at normal heat for each layer as you build up then press the final layer for the full time and temp this prevents overheating across applying multiple layers as well as shrinking every layer can shrink over the design so pressing for full time may not just impact adhesion but potentially cause shrinking and deformation of the design also consider thickness we generally recommend not layering more then 3-4 layers as the thickness will begin to build up and you may not prefer that final result for high multi-color or high layer designs inlay is usually your preferred method see our layering/inlay guide for more details and a project walkthrough × ok

thermoflex htv first create your design using a compatible vector software program and cut it in reverse using a vinyl cutter next weed the excess vinyl from your design and position it onto your fabric cover the design with a teflon sheet or piece of parchment paper and press it using a heat press or iron according to the manufacturers instructionsafter the vinyl has been applied and cooled application instructions of you particular thermoflex vinyl to find these instructions look at the product page that you bought your particular vinyl off of can you layer thermoflex it depends which thermoflex vinyl you have check the description of the product page of your vinyl how i cut thermoflex to cut thermoflex htv you will need a vinyl cutter or plotter a compatible vector software program and a cutting mat here are the general steps for cutting thermoflex htv: create your design in a compatible vector software program such as adobe illustrator or coreldraw be sure to mirror your design horizontally so that it appears in reverse load your thermoflex htv onto your cutting mat with the carrier sheet facing down be sure to smooth out any wrinkles or bubbles in the vinyl set your vinyl cutter or plotter to the appropriate settings for cutting thermoflex htv this may vary depending on the brand and model of your machine as well as the specific type of thermoflex htv you are using refer to the manufacturers instructions for best results send your design to the vinyl cutter or plotter and cut your design in reverse once your design is cut remove the excess vinyl from the carrier sheet using a weeding tool leaving only your desired design on the carrier sheet your thermoflex htv design is now ready to be applied to your fabric using a heat press or iron it is important to note that different types of thermoflex htv may have slightly different cutting instructions so be sure to carefully read and follow the instructions provided by the manufacturer for best results additionally be sure to test your design on a small area of fabric before cutting and pressing a larger design to ensure that you have the correct settings and application process can i apply glitter to thermoflex it is possible to add glitter to your thermoflex htv but we would recommend purchasing a glitter htv instead of adding it yourself do you peel thermoflex hot or cold it depends press every time think of supacolor as if screen print became best friends with digital print and cut what are custom screen print transfers / custom dtf transfers screen print transfers also known as screen-printed heat transfers or plastisol transfers are a popular method for creating high-quality durable designs on various fabric items including shirts they are essentially screen-printed designs that have been transferred onto a carrier paper allowing you to apply them to fabric using heatheres an overview of the process: design your artwork: create or select the design you want to transfer onto the fabric the design is typically created using graphic design software and should be suitable for screen printing prepare the screens: the screen printing process involves creating screens with the desired design this step typically requires specialized equipment and expertise the screens are coated with a photosensitive emulsion exposed to light through a film positive of the design and then washed to create the stencil print the transfers: once the screens are prepared the design is screen-printed onto a carrier paper using plastisol ink plastisol ink is a type of ink that does not dry or cure until heat is applied trim the transfers: after printing the transfers are trimmed around the design leaving a small border if desired this step is important to ensure precise placement on the fabric preheat your heat press: set your heat press to the appropriate temperature and time recommended by the transfer manufacturer the temperature and time will vary depending on the type of fabric and transfer being used position the transfer: place the fabric item on the heat press position the screen print transfer onto the fabric ensuring it is placed in the desired location apply heat and pressure: close the heat press and apply the recommended amount of pressure for the specified duration the combination of heat and pressure activates the plastisol ink causing it to transfer from the carrier paper onto the fabric peel and cool: after the specified time open the heat press and carefully peel off the carrier paper from the fabric the transferred design should be left on the fabric allow the fabric to cool down before handling or moving it screen print transfers offer several advantages including the ability to produce high-quality prints with vibrant colors fine details and durable results they can be created in advance allowing for efficient production and easy application when neededits important to note that the screen printing process for transfers requires specialized equipment materials and skills if you dont have experience with screen printing it may be more practical to work with a professional screen printing company that can create the transfers for you supacolor are the best heat transfers with excellent stretch & rebound; no cracking or fading even after 70+ washes × ok

account you can create an account by clicking here once you have signed up for an account with heat transfer warehouse you will start earning rewards when you make a purchase with your account what are the different vip tiers for rewardswe have bronze which is 1x point per $1 spent and 275 points for birthdays the second tier is gold when you spend $1250 with us you will be able to get 125x points per $1 spent an entry reward of 50 points and a birthday reward of 350 points the final tier platinum would be after spending $2500 and you get 125x points per $1 spent an entry reward of 100 points and a birthday reward of 400 points also you will get early access to sales and new products when i redeem a code does it expireyes the code expires after one year of redeeming it how can i redeem my rewardsgo to the rewards page and scroll down until you see the rewards you can also redeem your rewards once you are at checkout how to use redeemed codesonce you redeem your code and copy it from the rewards page you can redeem it in two ways the first way is in the cart screen; you would put the code in the discount area in the cart the second way is in the checkout screen under your items on the checkout page it says redeem your points then put the copied code into that area where can i see my balanceto view your balance you would need to log into your account then on the rewards page it will show you the number of points you have in your balance what happens to points earned on an order if i return the order unfortunately if you return an order the points you would have gained on that order will no longer be a part of your earned points have any other questions our chat system allows you to be connected with a customer service representative in seconds × ok

all accessories back peggy eraser 3 digital files back all digital files svgs pngs bundles sale rewards sign out contact us home bolt faqs bolt faqs what is bolt bolt is our checkout partner that helps us offer a faster more secure shopping experience once you create a bolt account youll unlock access to one-click checkout and easier login what are bolt passkeys passkeys give shoppers a fast and ultra-secure way to log in to their bolt account on mobile devices without having to enter a password instead passkeys utilize device-specific methods of verification including: pin: shopper uses a short code that is stored on their device to log in touch id: shopper uses their fingerprint instead of a password to log in face id: shopper uses facial recognition instead of a password to log in how do i create and use a bolt passkey shoppers can easily create a bolt passkey at accountboltcom once created shoppers can use their bolt passkey on their mobile devices across the bolt network how do i create an account while adding your shipping and billing info youll see a checked box that indicates your informations been saved bolt will send a verification code to your phone or email to verify your info the next time you check out you wont need a password or to fill out any fields allowing you to finish the purchase in seconds i already have an online account whats changing with bolt with bolt were pleased to offer: fast & secure one-click checkout a simpler login experience through text verification no more pesky passwords needed encrypted account protection so you can shop with peace of mind one account used across the bolt network so you can shop seamlessly across hundreds of brands how can i check out using my bolt account when youre ready to check out all youll need to do is enter the verification code sent to your phone or email this code allows us to offer a secure one-click checkout experience and replaces your account password can i still check out as a guest yes guest checkout is always available you do not need an account to check out simply click “continue as guest” during checkout how is my data kept secure shoppers trust and safety are important to us by creating an account bolt ensures that shoppers personal details are secure learn more about how bolt provides shopping with peace of mind where do i learn more about bolt head to bolt × ok

heat transfer warehouse always has the newest products and the largest in stock selection of heat transfer vinyl products if you are just starting out it can be a little overwhelming a few things to keep in mind when you are choosing a vinyl is the type of garment you are pressing on the finish you want your design to have and how many colors you want in your design the basics of htv care instructions - wait at least 24 hours before washing your freshly pressed garments - no fabric softeners as it will weaken the adhesive - for best results wash inside out in cold and line dry your garments other tips - most htv will need to have your design mirrored unless otherwise specified - if you are unsure on what side to cut peel a corner to reveal which side is the liner - always do a test cut on your htv to ensure your settings and blade are ready to go - weed your design on a warm bottom heat press platen to speed up weeding - for shiny polyester materials and coated polyester use a damp cloth with rubbing alcohol and gently apply it to the area on the garment you want to apply your design allow it to dry and apply your material this will allow the adhesive to better details of your order tracking order history live updates on your order minimum order: $1500 records heat transfer warehouse does not keep records before 2020 discounts only one code can be used per order splice in roll due to the manufacturing process rolls of material that are 5 yards or greater may have a splice in the roll done directly by the manufacturer splitting of rolls as of june 2022 heat transfer warehouse no longer offers slitting services converting of inventory due to normal conversion elements the material may slightly be off by 1/8 to 1 on all sizes of material processing order orders are processed monday through friday excluding all major holidays no orders are processed on weekends any order placed friday after the cut-off time by region saturday or sunday will be processed the following business day cut roll lenhs single yard orders in any quantity will be individual units example: if 3 yards of material is ordered 3 individual single yards will be shipped if ordering a non-standard roll lenh for example 7 yards we recommend ordering a 5-yard roll and 2 single yards for the best value if 7 single yards are ordered your material will be shipped in 7 individual 1-yard rolls priced at the single yard price drop ships in order to offer an expanded selection of specialized items heat transfer warehouse will drop ship these products direct from the manufacturer drop ships do incur a $1295 additional charge for shipping that covers additional shipping and handling charges from the manufacturer there are no guaranteed ship dates as the drop ship items will be fulfilled as the manufacturer is able drop ships ship ground only and will come separately from your primary order all drop ship items are labeled as such on our website and are non-returnable curbside pick-up orders curbside pickup is a flat rate fee for process/handling fees if curbside orders are not picked up within 3 business days the curbside order will be cancelled and in store credited if you need more time for pickup please reach out to our support team at: directions for curbside pick-up orders thank you for your curbside pick-up order our team at heat transfer warehouse is processing your order please follow the steps below for directions on your order: we will let you know when your order is ready this can take up to an hour or more we will email you once through friday per location time zone we do not offer pickups on the weekend clothing all clothing ships ground via ups clothing is available to ship to the 48 contiguous state and not available to ship to alaska hawaii or internationally these items may ship from any warehouse location across the country in order to fulfill the order and will always ship via ups ground service clothing may come in multiple packages orders with custom printed patterns all orders with digital fashion prints will be shipped from fargo nd no mask is included with your patterns this is a custom printed item shipping & terms all orders are placed online our warehouse is not open to the public heat transfer warehouse offers free freight on orders over $185 some restrictions apply based on product selection item and weight free ground freight applies only to the 48 contiguous states additional shipping costs may apply for canada alaska hawaii and puerto rico all orders are ship standard delivery from our warehouses in fargo nd; cincinnati oh/erlangerky las vegas nv; or jacksonville fl heat transfer warehouse does not ship to po boxes a physical address is required heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for package theft heat transfer warehouse reserves the right to send materials from any of our four 4 warehouses we will always try to ship from the warehouse closest to you delivery dates are monday-friday excluding all major holidays we do not deliver on saturdays or sundays fedex home delivery shipments may deliver on saturdays & sundays where applicable monitor your shipments using ups my choice or fedex delivery manager shipping options economy shipping flat rate: heat transfer warehouse will ship your order in a variety of ways to ensure you get your package via fedex or ups shipping options only available for orders less than $50 and below 7 pounds other restrictions may apply ground shipping: when this shipping method is chosen heat transfer warehouse will ship with the carrier of their choice either fedex or ups some restrictions apply i love ups: if this ground shipping method is chosen your package will be shipped ups additional fees may apply i love fedex ground/home: if this ground shipping method is chosen your package will be shipped to fedex additional fees may apply ups 2-day air: orders will be charged the live shipping rate for your location for a 2-business-day air shipping option this is a live-rate shipping option for your location based on the weight of materials ordered if this 2-day air shipment option is chosen all orders will be delivered in two 2 business days if an order is shipped on a friday using this method it will not deliver until the following tuesday unless a federal holiday is observed cut-off time for all 2-day air is 3:00 pm within your region 2:00 pm for the teal region on the map please see the map below for where your region falls additional fees may apply fedex 2 day air: orders will be charged the live shipping rate for your location for a 2 business-day air shipping option if this 2-day air shipment option is chosen all orders will be delivered in two 2 business days if an order is shipped on a friday using this method it will not deliver until the following tuesday unless a federal holiday is observed cut-off time for all 2-day air is 4:00 pm within your region 2:00 pm for the teal region on the map please see the map below for where your region falls additional fees may apply ups next day air: this live rate shipping option when chosen will be delivered the next business day by end of the day if an order is placed on friday with this option it will not arrive until the next business day monday unless a federal holiday is observed then it will arrive the following business day cut-off time for all standard overnight is 3:00 pm within your region 2:00 pm for the teal region on the map please see the map below for where your region falls if placing an overnight order after the cut-off time on thursday your order may not reach you until the following monday additional fees may apply fedex overnight: this live rate shipping option when chosen will be delivered the next business day before noon if an order is placed on friday with this option it will not arrive until the next business day monday unless a federal holiday is observed then it will arrive the following business day cut-off time for all standard overnight is 3:00 pm within your region 2:00 pm for the teal region on the map please see the map below for where your region falls if placing an overnight order after the cut-off time on thursday your order may not reach you until the following monday additional fees may apply overnight saturday delivery: all orders are processed monday through friday excluding major holidays when this shipping method is chosen heat transfer warehouse will ship at their discretion with whichever carrier will deliver to your area on saturday the cut-off time for orders to be placed for saturday delivery is friday by 3:00 pm within your region 2:00 pm for the teal region on the map if the saturday option is chosen monday-thursday the order will ship priority overnight for delivery the following business day and will not be held until friday for a saturday delivery some exclusions may apply and additional fees may apply curbside pick up: curbside pickup is a flare rate fee for process/handling fees roadie same day delivery: orders must be placed monday - friday before 1pm per warehouse location add-ons & changes heat transfer warehouse asks that you double-check the order in your cart and the shipping address to ensure everything is correct before placing the order once an order has been placed we are unable to make any changes or cancellations due to how fast we process orders incorrect address: heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for items that could not be shipped to their destination because of an incorrect or undeliverable address if you have made an error in entering the shipping address we ask that you reach out to fedex or ups and have it held at a location for easy pickup near you this policy is not our preference nor is it our first choice the simplest solution to this problem is to carefully enter and review your address as you place your order heat transfer warehouse does not change addresses on order damaged / lost / delayed package checking orders: in the unlikely event of a missing or incorrect product heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for expedited shipping please check your order within three 3 days of receiving it and contact heat transfer warehouse immediately of any issues if you are sheeting or converting our materials heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for any loss of materials if you feel the material is short please measure and contact us before you cut the material goods damaged in transit: in the instance that goods are damaged or the order is incomplete the package may be refused by the customer all shipments are deemed to have been received in good order unless we are notified in writing within a period of three 3 days following the delivery of the goods packages lost by carrier: in the instance that goods are lost in transit please notify heat transfer warehouse within forty-eight 48 hours of the tracking being marked as delivered and/or determining it has been lost or stolen heat transfer warehouse will reach out to the carrier service for a trace on the package after the trace is completed which may take up to three 3 business days heat transfer warehouse will either replace the material or give in-store credit if deemed lost/stolen replacement of materials is not guaranteed and is at the sole discretion of heat transfer warehouse if materials are replaced heat transfer warehouse will have your items shipped to a fedex hold location or ups access point delayed orders: if a delivery attempt is made any time within the delivery window and it is not delivered because the customer is not available or the business is closed heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for delays in the shipping commitment overnight shipping: heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for weather related delays stock production times all orders with printed htv or psv patterns can take 24-48 hours for production and will be shipped from our fargo nd location all stock rhinestones can take 24-48 hours for production and will be shipped from our fargo nd location custom rhinestone sublimation htv dtf and sticker orders: all orders will receive a confirmation email from an artist within 1 business day of receiving the order all orders have to be approved before going into production once an order is approved production can take up to 24-48 hours and will be shipped from our fargo nd location custom supacolor: all orders will be processed by an artist within 1 business day of receiving the order please note any artwork issues can delay the process and production times an artist will reach out to either confirm your order is into production if you selected a proof or if there is an artwork concern once the order has been sent to production it is 2-4 business days production followed by the shipping method selected at check out custom decopress patches: all orders will be processed by an artist within 1 business day of receiving the order please note any artwork issues can delay the process and production times an artist will reach out to either confirm your order is into production if you selected a proof or if there is an artwork concern once the order has been sent to production it is 3-5 business days production followed by fedex 2day air shipping products not applicable for free shipping dropships: in order to offer an expanded selection of specialized items heat transfer warehouse will drop ship these products direct from the manufacturer dropships do incur a fee that covers manufacturer is able dropships ship ground ups only and will come separately from your primary order all drop-ship items are labeled as such on our website clothing: all clothing ships ground via ups all clothing will receive a $1295 shipping charge these items may ship from any warehouse location across the country in order to fulfill the order and will always ship via ups ground service clothing may come in multiple packages tracking will be emailed to you once the order has been shipped supacolor: all supacolor orders are a dropship item and will have a separate shipping charge all shipping receive any remaining funds as store credit we do not accept returns after 30 days all returned items are expected to be back to our warehouse within 15 business days of receiving the order some exclusions may apply returns received to our warehouse after 15 business days or without an rma will be denied if the return is denied you will be asked to pay return shipping for it to be returned to you if the denied return is not claimed within 30 days it will be considered abandoned we do not offer exchanges or returns on clothing dropships and equipment for approved returns due to the nature of our business and the materials shipped we can only provide store credit for approved returns some exclusions may apply excludes equipment clothing and dropships heat transfer warehouse will deduct appropriate shipping and handling charges a 15% to 20% restocking fee may be assessed where applicable heat transfer warehouse is not responsible for damaged packages/material upon return damaged material will be refused please make sure the material is packaged correctly and safely to ensure no damage happens while in transit returns made on packs of transfer paper inkjet laser dye-sub that have been opened will be given in store credit on the cost of the pack minus the sheets used if you return an item on an order where you received points those points will be deducted from your account once this item is returned if you use your waladolla$ discount code on an order and then return a product you will get the balance back in store credit for your product minus the discount that was used all returns will be shipped via ups with a return authorization label please allow 3-6 business days for your return to be processed once received by heat transfer warehouse non-returnable items warehouse will assist in communication with the manufacturer as needed defective products all defective products issues must be addressed with heat transfer warehouse within 15 business days of material heat transfer warehouse will give store credit only there will be no refunds on defective material if heat transfer warehouse is not notified within 15 days of the arrival of defective material no replacement will be sent out steps to return items submit request for an rma from our customer service team print out rma label and place it on the box to send back ups shipment please live in by looking for unique and important ways to give back through our time and donations help us help our communities thrive heat transfer warehouse is dedicated to seeing the community where we work to continue to thrive help us partner with charities and businesses across the region to bring coats to kids in the fargo public schools help families combat homelessness and give christmas to those in need with your support we are able to continue our charitable efforts with both time and money co-owner tricia barse says “we are grateful as a company for the community we live in to be able to give back in some small way and help make someone elses life a little better is my mission in life” jacksonville fl florida service dogs inc of jacksonville florida is a veteran founded and operated organization that provides education advocacy and professionally trained service animals to people who qualify our jacksonville team were able to help socialize the service dogs by walking and playing with the service dogs _____________________________________________________________________________________ cincinnati oh the emergency shelter of northern kentuckys mission statement reads to provide life-saving and life-changing low barrier shelter and services for adults in our community our cincinnati team was grateful for the opportunity to help prepare lunches for the community _____________________________________________________________________________________ fargo nd hope blooms is solving a problem one in which people can feel forgotten or unimportant with a beautiful but simple message of “you matter” hope blooms repurposes donated flowers and rearranges them into beautiful bedside bouquets so that those who are in need most in our community feel this sense of inclusion _____________________________________________________________________________________ fargo nd the great north pole helps children and families in need in eastern north dakota and through the tunnel the lenh of the race is about 2 times the lenh as the tunnel they ran through on that september day this point on as htw respects your privacy you can browse most of the htw website without identifying yourself or revealing any personal information once you choose to provide us with any information by which you can be identified you can be assured that it will only be used to support your customer relationship with htwthis statement regarding the privacy of the personally identifiable information you provide online covers five main areas: knowledge preference accuracy & access security and administration knowledge htw provides this online privacy statement and other policy statements to make you aware of our privacy policy and practices and of the choices you can make about the way your information is collected and used to make this notice easy to find it is available on the bottom of every web page in which we collect information from you what we collect on some htw web pages you may be able to make requests and register to receive materials the types of personal information collected at these pages are name contact and/or billing information transaction and phone numbers or email addresses in order to tailor our subsequent communications to you and continuously improve our products and services we may also ask you to voluntarily provide us with information regarding your personal or professional interests demographics experience with our products and contact preferences when you make a purchase you are given the option of logging into an account or checking out as a guest in either case when you purchase a product you will provide us with information such as your name email address phone number and shipping address we use bolt financial inc as our checkout service provider personal information collected by bolt is subject to bolts privacy policy which can be found here how we use it htw uses your information to better understand your needs and provide you with better service specifically we use your information to help you complete a transaction to communicate with you to update you on service and benefits and to personalize our web site for you from time to time we may also use your information to provide you with marketing information we think would be of particular interest at a minimum we will always give you the opportunity to opt out of receiving such direct marketing or market research contact who we share it with htw will not sell rent or lease your personally identifiable information to others unless we have your permission or are required by law we will not share the personal data you provide online preference htw will not use or share the personally identifiable information provided to us online in ways unrelated to the ones described above without first informing you and offering you a choice as previously stated we will also provide you the opportunity to let us know if you do not wish to receive unsolicited direct marketing materials from us and we will do everything we can to honor such requests local country laws and policies are applied where they differ from those in the us your permission is always secured first should we ever share your information with third parties that are not acting on our behalf and governed by our privacy policy accuracy & access htw strives to keep your personally identifiable information accurate we will provide you with access to your information including making reasonable efforts to provide you with online access to your registration data so that you may view update or correct your information at the htw site to protect your privacy and security we will also take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting you access or enabling you to make corrections to access your individually identifiable information
